Why is this one Keter? Is it because there is probably another one out there somewhere, uncontained? It still seems odd that this artifact should be considered anything other than safe, when it's containment procedures currently amount to essentially .

Also as a bit of input for somebody not familiar with the canon of which this is apparently a part, this one was pretty impenetrable. The actual skip itself seemed fairly straightforward (as skips go), so I was with you through the description and all that. But the logman, I read through it once normally, then once carefully, then read a few parts again, and it was confusing and odd in the bad way. It wasn't badly done, I just had a strong suspicion that I lacked the context of some larger canon of stories to make any sense of the randomness going on there, and reading the comments seems to confirm that.

If it is just your intention to write this so that people who already know the canon can understand it and the rest of us aren't really meant to get much out of it, I understand that and accept it. I'm no-voting because I think the article is fine if that is the intent. But if you are interested in having it be less completely random for those who aren't versed in the backstory, I think it could benefit from some edits to make things a bit less overwhelming for someone coming in blind.







